# Critical extraction note: doc-gen4 uses **Lean 4
# Cli `FLAGS:` / `ARGS:` / `SUBCOMMANDS:` section
# DSL** at Main.lean:154+ — the `[Cli|...]` macro
# parses three optional sections: `FLAGS:` with
# `short, long : Type; "help"` (or `short, long;
# "help"` for booleans), `ARGS:` with `name : Type;
# "help"` (or `...name : Type; "help"` for
# variadics), `SUBCOMMANDS:` with named subcommand
# defs.  Distinct from R313 Idris 2 `MkOpt ['?',
# 'h'] ["help"] (NoArg Help) "Show help"` (single
# constructor), R310 Fortran M_CLI2 single-string-
# packed spec.  Lean 4 Cli's approach: SECTIONED-
# DSL — corpus's **first documented sectioned-
# DSL-spec CLI pattern**.
#
# Critical extraction note: doc-gen4 uses **Lean 4
# Cli `...name : Type` variadic-prefix pattern**
# at Main.lean:175, 205 — `...source : String;
# "..."` and `...modules : String; "..."` mark
# positionals as VARIABLE-ARITY (one-or-more
# values).  The `...` prefix is consumed by the
# `[Cli|...]` macro and elaborated to a `Variable
# ArgsAs` accessor.  Distinct from R311 Guile `(arg
# ...)` rest-args (Scheme), R313 Idris 2 `Param.
# str_list({ name: "packages" })` (typed
# constructor), R310 Fortran M_CLI2 (comma-
# separated array via single flag).  Lean 4 Cli's
# approach: `...` PREFIX FOR VARIADIC POSITIONALS
# — corpus's **first documented `...`-prefix-for-
# variadic CLI pattern**.
